2026-01-03 13:58:57,825 - CPU: 0.0%, Memory: 79.1% - openai._base_client - DEBUG - Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'system', 'content': [{'type': 'text', 'text': 'You are an Information Gathering Agent for the **2048 (2048)**.\nYour SOLE task is to analyze the input (screenshot/context) and extract the required game state data.'}]}, {'role': 'user', 'content': [{'type': 'text', 'text': ''}, {'type': 'text', 'text': '\n\n--- Input Data ---\n'}, {'type': 'text', 'text': 'This is a screenshot of the current moment in the game with grid augmentation to help you understand it better.'}, {'type': 'text', 'text': '\n\nCurrent task:\n通过滑动合并数字方块，尝试达到2048或更高的数字，获得最高分数。\n\n\n\n--- Information to Extract ---\nDescription: Provide a detailed description of the current game state, focusing on the following aspects:\n1. **The \'Anchor\' Corner:** Identify the location of the largest tile (e.g., \'The 1024 tile is anchored in the bottom-right corner\').\n2. **The \'Monotonic Wall\':** Describe the descending numerical sequence of the tiles along the row/column adjacent to the anchor corner (e.g., \'The bottom row is ordered: 1024, 512, 256, 128\').\n3. **The \'Trapped Tile\':** If present, identify the specific tile (its value and location) that is trapped between two higher-value tiles, preventing future merges.\n4. **The \'New Tile Threat\':** Describe the location of the new tile (e.g., \'A \'2\' appears in the top-middle cell, which could trap the \'4\' tile in the top-left corner\').\n5. **The \'Highest Value Tile\':** Report the highest value tile on the board and its position.\n\n\n\n**Critical Failure Indicator:** If the description mentions a tile that is trapped or the \'Monotonic Wall\' is violated, this signals a high-risk state requiring immediate correction.\n- **Anchor_Corner_Value:** The value of the largest tile and its fixed corner position (e.g., \'1024 (bottom-right)\').\n- **Monotonic_Wall_State:** The descending numerical order of the tiles along the \'Monotonic Wall\' (e.g., \'1024, 512, 256, 128\').\n- **Trapped_Tile_Location:** The cell position of the tile that is trapped between two higher-value tiles.\n- **Highest_Value_Tile:** The value of the highest tile on the board and its position.\n- **New_Tile_Location:** The cell position of the newly spawned tile.\n- **Critical_Failure:** A simple \'Yes\' or \'No\' indicating if the state is critically compromised (e.g., \'Yes\' if a trapped tile or monotonicity violation exists).\nError_message: Any visible in-game error message (e.g., "Game Over", "Invalid Move"), otherwise, only output "null".\nOther: Other relevant information that does not fit the above categories, otherwise, only output "null".\n\n\n\n--- OUTPUT FORMAT ---\nYou should only respond in the exact format described below and not output comments, Markdown, code fences, or other information.\nDescription:\n<A detailed description>\nAnchor_Corner_Value: <The value and position of the largest tile>\nMonotonic_Wall_State: <The descending sequence of the \'Monotonic Wall\'>\nTrapped_Tile_Location: <The position of the trapped tile, or \'None\' if none>\nHighest_Value_Tile: <The value and position of the highest tile>\nNew_Tile_Location: <The position of the new tile>\nCritical_Failure: <Yes or No indicating a high-risk state>\nError_message:\n<The text of the error message, otherwise "null">\nOther:\n<Other information is ..., otherwise "null">'}]}], 'model': 'qwen3-vl-plus', 'max_tokens': 1024, 'temperature': 0.0}}
